The paper deals with the complexity of computing locally optimal solutions for weighted versions of standard set problems, which are typically studied in the areas of algorithms, data structures, and combinatorial optimization. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) are likely sub-categories. The paper also uses the framework of PLS (Polynomial Local Search), which is a popular technique in the field of artificial intelligence and machine learning, suggesting that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves analyzing the performance of local search algorithms, which is a topic of interest in the area of machine learning and optimization, indicating that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a potential sub-category as well.
